{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"06793a7a150c79fb5d5690b8e2d4bf09","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All data gathered. Now I have enough to write the stack_v1.md.\n\nKey insights from research:\n\n**D-030 Next.js 16 + Turbopack:**\n- ✅ Turbopack stable as default in 16.0 (Oct 2025), 16.2 (Mar 2026) fixed many bugs\n- ⚠️ 16.2.6+ recommended; 16.0/16.1 had real edge cases\n- ⚠️ Build memory: 7168MB heap + Enhanced builder 16GB on Vercel\n- ⚠️ Custom webpack config silently ignored under Turbopack — opt-out via `NEXT_DISABLE_TURBOPACK=1` for problematic cases\n- ✅ App Router + Server Components + RSC all supported\n- ✅ React Compiler stable (auto-memoization)\n- ✅ Image defaults changed (60s→4h cache, qualities [75], removed size 16)\n- For Akasha (PWA, no custom webpack, server-side heavy with RAG + SSE): Turbopack ✅\n\n**D-031 DB + pgvector:**\n- ✅ pgvector default for SMB RAG, < 2M vectors\n- ✅ Akasha corpus: Cabala + Numerologia + Astrologia + Tantra + Odu + I Ching = ~1-10k entries initially → far under 5M\n- ✅ Postgres already in stack (auth + relational data)\n- ✅ Cost: 6× lower than Pinecone at SMB scale\n- ✅ Same transaction boundary (vector + relational in 1 query)\n- ⚠️ p95 ~65ms (acceptable; LLM dominates end-to-end)\n- Alternative: Weaviate for hybrid BM25+vector (Akasha needs BOTH symbolic search for proper names AND semantic)\n- **Decision: pgvector primary, Meilisearch/Typesense for lexical proper-name search (Pilar names, Orixás, I Ching hex names)**\n\n**D-032 LLM:**\n- Sonnet 4.6 (R$ 3 in / R$ 15 out) — best cost/quality for production RAG\n- Prompt cache 90% saving on repeated persona + Grimório context\n- Sonnet > GPT-4o for: long context (1M stable), SWE-bench, tool calls (91%), JSON compliance (99.2%)\n- GPT-4o wins: vision, HumanEval, TTFT p50\n- For Akasha: Sonnet 4.6 primary, Haiku 4.5 for crisis detection (cheaper, fast), Opus 4.7 for synthesis moments\n- **Mentor persona needs: RAG-grounded, PT-BR, ethical guardrails, structured output (Mandato JSON) → Sonnet 4.6 ideal**\n- Minimax M3 fallback (this codebase) for offline/cheaper ops\n- Streaming mandatory (Claude API SSE)\n\n**D-033 SSE vs WebSocket:**\n- ✅ SSE wins for AI streaming (90% of use case)\n- ✅ HTTP-native, proxy-friendly, auto-reconnect\n- ✅ For Vercel: SSE works only on Edge Runtime; WebSocket not supported at all\n- ✅ Decision: SSE for Mentor streaming + Mandato push notifications\n- WebSocket NOT needed (no collab editing, no multiplayer, no chat between users)\n- Latency benchmarks: SSE ≈ WebSocket for LLM throughput (50-100 tok/s)\n\n**D-034 Auth:**\n- Options: Better Auth / Supabase Auth / Clerk / Auth.js v5\n- Akasha needs: own user data (LGPD), PT-BR/Mercosur region, RLS for multi-tenant future, MFA, ~100k MAU 5y\n- Supabase Auth: 50k MAU free, R$ 25/mo after, RLS native, EU data residency, but couple us to Supabase\n- Better Auth: 100k MAU ~$50/mo, TypeScript-native, owns user data, no RLS (app-layer)\n- Auth.js v5: free, owns data, but still beta (or pin to v4)\n- Clerk: $1,025/mo at 100k MAU — too expensive, US-only data\n- **Decision: Supabase Auth (already aligned with Supabase Postgres), OR Better Auth if we want to own the user table on the same Postgres**\n- Given LGPD + future Mercosur expansion + RAG RLS use case → Supabase Auth\n\n**D-035 Payments (Stripe):** Already in place, keep.\n\n**D-036 Deploy:**\n- Vercel: $20/seat/mo Pro, best DX, Edge <50ms, Turbopack cache, $40/100GB overage. SSE works on Edge. WebSocket NOT supported.\n- Railway: $5 starter, $5 included resources, includes Postgres, supports long-running processes, can run WebSocket if needed\n- Render: $7+, free tier sleeps (bad for prod)\n- Hetzner: $5-12/mo, full control, no edge, needs ops\n- Brazil/Latam: AWS São Paulo region (sa-east-1) for LGPD data residency\n- **Decision: Vercel Pro (main app) + Supabase Cloud (Postgres + pgvector + Auth) for prod. Cost ~$45-60/mo MVP. Migration to Hetzner + Coolify if MAU > 50k.**\n\n**Bonus: D-037 ORM (Prisma 7 vs Drizzle):**\n- Prisma 7 (Nov 2025) dropped Rust engine, 14MB→1.6MB bundle, native edge support\n- Project ALREADY uses Prisma 7 (per CLAUDE.md memory)\n- Drizzle better for: edge runtime, smallest bundle, SQL-native\n- Prisma better for: migrations (battle-tested), DX, team onboarding\n- **Decision: Keep Prisma 7 — already in stack, mature migrations, native edge support now**\n\nNow let me write the artifact. ~600+ lines with sources cited.","signature":"b7b3298a6964ff8f883f4511cf12f66652ced0d013a724883638ebac6b1bc600"}],"model":"MiniMax-M3","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard"},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2945538a-1ae9-4d96-ab14-ea18f9fcf943","uuid":"f6306791-9a1d-4bba-a488-067489f96f8f"}
